<figureCitation box="[760,830,153,179]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1934,1959]" captionTargetBox="[167,1421,178,1915]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[166,1421,166,1915]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Heliothrips longisensibilis sp. n. (1) Female; (2) Teneral Female; (3) Male; (4) Head and pronotum; (5) Abdominal tergites IV–VI; (6) Prospinasternum; (7) Abdominal tergite I; (8) Abdominal sternites III–IV of male; (9) Abdominal tergites VIII–X of male; (10) Fore wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335016/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="149">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). Body brown but with terminal abdominal segments paler (
<figureCitation box="[225,288,189,216]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1934,1959]" captionTargetBox="[167,1421,178,1915]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[166,1421,166,1915]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Heliothrips longisensibilis sp. n. (1) Female; (2) Teneral Female; (3) Male; (4) Head and pronotum; (5) Abdominal tergites IV–VI; (6) Prospinasternum; (7) Abdominal tergite I; (8) Abdominal sternites III–IV of male; (9) Abdominal tergites VIII–X of male; (10) Fore wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335016/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="149">Fig.3</figureCitation>
). Abdominal tergite IX with three pairs of stout thorn-like setae and the base of anterior pair nearly contiguous, each posterior pair of setae slightly slender and lateral to preceding pair (
<figureCitation box="[1103,1171,225,251]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1934,1959]" captionTargetBox="[167,1421,178,1915]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[166,1421,166,1915]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Heliothrips longisensibilis sp. n. (1) Female; (2) Teneral Female; (3) Male; (4) Head and pronotum; (5) Abdominal tergites IV–VI; (6) Prospinasternum; (7) Abdominal tergite I; (8) Abdominal sternites III–IV of male; (9) Abdominal tergites VIII–X of male; (10) Fore wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335016/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="149">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
). Sternites III–VII each with a transverse oblong pore plate (
<figureCitation box="[559,628,261,287]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1934,1959]" captionTargetBox="[167,1421,178,1915]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[166,1421,166,1915]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Heliothrips longisensibilis sp. n. (1) Female; (2) Teneral Female; (3) Male; (4) Head and pronotum; (5) Abdominal tergites IV–VI; (6) Prospinasternum; (7) Abdominal tergite I; (8) Abdominal sternites III–IV of male; (9) Abdominal tergites VIII–X of male; (10) Fore wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335016/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="149">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
